<paragraph id="8BEF36B4FFA8FFBAB092894CFB40F967" blockId="8.[136,1452,1545,1712]" pageId="8" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis id="B924EAA6FFA8FFBAB092894CF909F9D6" bold="true" box="[136,260,1545,1567]" pageId="8" pageNumber="83">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C504D37FFA8FFBAB110894FFA5DF9D7" authority="Etayo &amp; Pino-Bodas, 2021" authorityName="Etayo &amp; Pino-Bodas" authorityYear="2021" box="[266,592,1546,1567]" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Adelococcaceae" genus="Pseudopyrenidium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Verrucariales" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="epipertusariae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B924EAA6FFA8FFBAB110894FFA5DF9D7" box="[266,592,1546,1567]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="83">Pseudopyrenidium epipertusariae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21757DDFFA8FFBAB24D894FFAAEF9D7" box="[599,675,1546,1567]" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(holotypus teleomorph, hb. Etayo 31122 anamorph). A, B, habitus of perithecia immersed in thallus and apothecia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D37FFA8FFBAB1EF896BFAA7F98B" box="[501,682,1582,1603]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Pertusaria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pertusariales" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="pertusa">
<emphasis id="B924EAA6FFA8FFBAB1EF896BFAA7F98B" box="[501,682,1582,1603]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="83">Pertusaria pertusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that turns violet with the parasite. C, longitudinal section of ascomatal wall (in KOH). D, section of hymenium with mature spores in an ascus. E, ascospores with 2–4 septa to submurales. F, habitus with immersed subspherical conidiomata on 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D37FFA8FFBAB1B38933FA6DF943" box="[425,608,1654,1675]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Pertusaria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pertusariales" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="pertusa">
<emphasis id="B924EAA6FFA8FFBAB1B38933FA6DF943" box="[425,608,1654,1675]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="83">Pertusaria pertusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. G, conidiomatal wall in section and conidiogenous cells. H, I, conidia first hyaline, finally brownish. Scales A, B, G = 100 um; C, D, E, F, G, H &amp; I = 10 µm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BEF36B4FFA8FFBAB0A7899BFBF2F83D" blockId="8.[136,1452,1758,2037]" pageId="8" pageNumber="83">
Discussion: So far only one species was known in the genus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D37FFA8FFBAB36E899AFC04F930" authorityName="Navarro-Rosines, Zhurbenko &amp; Cl. Roux" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Linds." box="[884,1033,1758,1784]" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Adelococcaceae" genus="Pseudopyrenidium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Verrucariales" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="tartaricola">
<emphasis id="B924EAA6FFA8FFBAB36E899AFC04F930" box="[884,1033,1758,1784]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="83">P. tartaricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
growing only on 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D37FFA8FFBAB4CE899BFD52F930" authorityName="Massalongo" authorityYear="1852" box="[1236,1375,1758,1784]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Ochrolechiaceae" genus="Ochrolechia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pertusariales" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAA6FFA8FFBAB4CE899BFD52F930" box="[1236,1375,1758,1784]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="83">Ochrolechia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It has many features in common with 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D37FFA8FFBAB1E68846FAB3F8D4" authorityName="Etayo &amp; Pino-Bodas" authorityYear="2021" box="[508,702,1795,1820]" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Adelococcaceae" genus="Pseudopyrenidium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Verrucariales" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="epipertusariae">
<emphasis id="B924EAA6FFA8FFBAB1E68846FAB3F8D4" box="[508,702,1795,1820]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="83">P. epipertusariae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs by its larger perithecia 250–300(–400) µm, a thicker perithecial wall (30–)40–50 µm and very variable but larger ellipsoidal ascospores, (14–)18–26(–27) × (7–)9–11(–13) µm, first with 1–2 septa, later with 3–5 transversal septa. No spores with 5 septa have been found in 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D37FFA8FFBAB4FC880EFDA9F8AC" authorityName="Etayo &amp; Pino-Bodas" authorityYear="2021" box="[1254,1444,1867,1892]" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Adelococcaceae" genus="Pseudopyrenidium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Verrucariales" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="epipertusariae">
<emphasis id="B924EAA6FFA8FFBAB4FC880EFDA9F8AC" box="[1254,1444,1867,1892]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="83">P. epipertusariae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Conidiomata have never been found in 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D37FFA8FFBAB25F882AFAD7F840" authorityName="Navarro-Rosines, Zhurbenko &amp; Cl. Roux" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Linds." box="[581,730,1902,1928]" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Adelococcaceae" genus="Pseudopyrenidium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Verrucariales" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="tartaricola">
<emphasis id="B924EAA6FFA8FFBAB25F882AFAD7F840" box="[581,730,1902,1928]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="83">P. tartaricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B45FFA8FFBAB2F0882BFC21F840" author="Navarro-Rosines, P. &amp; Zhurbenko, M. P. &amp; Roux, C." box="[746,1068,1902,1928]" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" pagination="129 - 140" refId="ref8814" refString="Navarro-Rosines, P., Zhurbenko, M. P. &amp; Roux, C. (2010) Pseudopyrenidium nova genro por inkludi Weddellomyces tartaricola (nelikeniginta fungo likenloga, Ascomycota) - Pseudopyrenidium un nouveau genre pour inclure Weddellomyces tartaricola (champignon lichenicole non lichenise, Ascomycota). Bulletin de la societe Linneenne de Provence 61: 129 - 140." type="journal article" year="2010">
Navarro-Rosinés 
<emphasis id="B924EAA6FFA8FFBAB3AB882AFBE7F840" box="[945,1002,1902,1928]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="83">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B45FFA8FFBAB42D882BFDADF840" author="Navarro-Rosines, P. &amp; Etayo, J." box="[1079,1440,1902,1929]" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" pagination="69 - 76" refId="ref8759" refString="Navarro-Rosines, P. &amp; Etayo, J. (2018) Sobre la presencia de Pseudopyrenidium tartaricola (Eurotiomycetes, hongos liquenicolas) en los Pirineos. Revista Catalana de Micologia 39: 69 - 76. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 13225 - 012 - 0166 - 9" type="journal article" year="2018">Navarro-Rosinés &amp; Etayo 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Microscopical features of the anamorph remind 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D37FFA8FFBAB2B588D7FAF3F864" authorityName="Saccardo" authorityYear="1880" box="[687,766,1938,1964]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Didymellaceae" genus="Phoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus" sensu="lato">
<emphasis id="B924EAA6FFA8FFBAB2B588D7FAF3F864" box="[687,766,1938,1964]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="83">Phoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21757DDFFA8FFBAB31D88D7FB31F864" box="[775,828,1938,1964]" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" sensu="lato">s.lat.</taxonomicNameLabel>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D37FFA8FFBAB37F88D7FDAAF865" authority="Sydow &amp; P. Sydow (1916: 369)" authorityName="Sydow &amp; P. Sydow" authorityPageNumber="369" authorityYear="1916" box="[869,1447,1938,1965]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Didymosphaeriaceae" genus="Microsphaeropsis" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAA6FFA8FFBAB37F88D7FC20F864" box="[869,1069,1938,1964]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="83">Microsphaeropsis</emphasis>
Sydow &amp; P. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B45FFA8FFBAB4D288D7FDAAF865" author="Sydow, H. &amp; Sydow, P." box="[1224,1447,1938,1965]" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" pagination="353 - 375" refId="ref9435" refString="Sydow, H. &amp; Sydow, P. (1916) Weitere Diagnosen neuer philippinischer Pilze. Annales Mycologie 14: 353 - 375." type="journal article" year="1916">Sydow (1916: 369)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, genera including several lichenicolous species. So far, no lichenicolous species of those genera have been collected on 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D37FFA8FFBAB092889EF90DF83C" authorityName="DC. In Lamarck &amp; de Candolle" authorityYear="1805" box="[136,256,2011,2036]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Pertusaria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pertusariales" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAA6FFA8FFBAB092889EF90DF83C" box="[136,256,2011,2036]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="83">Pertusaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Phylogenetically this species is not related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D37FFA8FFBAB317889FFBA9F83C" authorityName="Vainio" authorityYear="1921" box="[781,932,2010,2036]" class="Polycystina" family="Coccodiscidae" genus="Didymocyrtis" kingdom="Chromista" order="Spumellaria" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAA6FFA8FFBAB317889FFBA9F83C" box="[781,932,2010,2036]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="83">Didymocyrtis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="136B2A31FFA8FFBAB3AE889FFBFCF83D" box="[948,1009,2010,2037]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[136,234,1969,1991]" captionTargetBox="[189,1397,243,1926]" captionTargetId="figure-41@6.[189,1397,241,1926]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Phylogeny of Pleosporales based on ITS rDNA and LSU rDNA. This is a 50% consensus majority tree from the Bayesian analyses. Branches supported with posterior probability ≥ 0.95 and bootstrap ≥ 70% are indicated in bold. Bootstrap and posterior probabilities values indicated at branches supported only in one analysis (ML or Bayesian analysis)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5423308" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5423308/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="83">Fig.1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
